---
import ProjectDetailLayout from '../../../layouts/ProjectDetailLayout.astro';

const frontmatter = {
  title: 'Azygo',
  description: 'The ERP and mobile application that reinvent student-union management to free up energy for campus life.',
  heroImage: '/images/azygo.png',
  projectCategory: 'Mobile & ERP project',
  technologies: ['Laravel','Vue.js','Flutter','Docker Swarm','Figma'],
  links: [{ label: 'Visit website', url: 'https://azygo.fr/', variant: 'primary' }],
  parentLink: '/en/projects',
  theme: {
    accent: "#ff3f6b",
    accentSoft: "#f2ebe3",
    glowA: "rgba(255, 63, 107, 0.32)",
    glowB: "rgba(255, 138, 92, 0.26)",
    titleFont: "Roundo, 'Poppins', 'Manrope', sans-serif",
    bodyFont: "'Poppins', 'Manrope', sans-serif",
  },
  fontImports: ["https://fonts.cdnfonts.com/css/roundo"],
};
---

<ProjectDetailLayout frontmatter={frontmatter}>
  <h2>Mission</h2>
  <p>To address the administrative overload faced by student unions, we designed <strong>AZYGO</strong>: a digital ecosystem created to give time back to student engagement. Our solution combines a centralized ERP and an intuitive mobile application so teams can focus on their real mission: <strong>building vibrant campus communities</strong>.</p>

  <h2>A robust architecture</h2>
  <p>Built by a team of three passionate developers, AZYGO relies on a modern technical stack designed for performance and scalability:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Backend</strong>: a robust <strong>Laravel</strong> API (PHP) to secure data and orchestrate business logic.</li>
    <li><strong>Admin frontend</strong>: a reactive dashboard built with <strong>Vue.js</strong> for real-time operations and configuration.</li>
    <li><strong>Mobile</strong>: a smooth native-feeling iOS/Android experience powered by <strong>Flutter</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>Infrastructure</strong>: high availability through <strong>Docker Swarm</strong> orchestration and secure networking via WireGuard.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Key features</h2>
  <h3>For admins (ERP)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Ticketing & memberships</strong>: simplified workflow management.</li>
    <li><strong>Accounting</strong>: real-time financial tracking.</li>
    <li><strong>Coordination</strong>: centralized event planning and team needs.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>For students (app)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>A dedicated campus activity feed.</li>
    <li>An integrated online store for student-union merchandising.</li>
    <li>Targeted notifications so users never miss important events.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Product methodology</h2>
  <p>Our approach focused on field feedback to keep the product relevant and practical:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Immersion</strong>: gathering needs directly from student-union teams.</li>
    <li><strong>UX design</strong>: iterative prototyping in Figma to validate usability.</li>
    <li><strong>Continuous delivery</strong>: integration and deployments through GitLab CI/CD.</li>
    <li><strong>Feedback loop</strong>: constant improvements driven by real usage data.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>Result: optimized management for student unions and better experiences for students. <strong>AZYGO</strong> is not just a tool — it is a partner for campus life.</p>
</ProjectDetailLayout>
